    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-07-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="332"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d332">
                <head>No. 328.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Jackson</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-07-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 30, 1886</date>. (Received August
                        7.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 280.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith a copy of
                    note written by me to Mr. Mariscal, in the matter of the killing of Francisco
                    Arresures, under instruction brought by your telegram of 29th instant.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HENRY R. JACKSON.</signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 280.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Jackson</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Mariscal</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-07-30">
                                <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 30, 1886</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: By telegram received from the Secretary of
                        State, at Washington, I am informed that Francisco Arresures, an American
                        citizen, was delivered, upon requisition, to the authorities of Mexico,
                        notwithstanding his American citizenship, by a Texan magistrate; that the
                        American consul at Piedras Negras made demand upon the former for his
                        return, which was refused, and by their order the said Francispo Arresures
                        was taken from jail and shot.</p>
                    <pb facs="0793" n="709" xml:id="pg_709"/>
                    <p>I regret that I cannot specify dates and places of the delivery, demand, and
                        killing. It will suffice, however, to say that the occurrences are very
                        recent, and must have been in the close vicinage of Piedras Negras.</p>
                    <p>I am instructed by my Government to ask that a prompt investigation may be
                        made of them, and that should they expose a case of violence, the criminals
                        may be brought to justice.</p>
                    <p>It gives me pleasure to renew, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>HENRY R. JACKSON.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
